> Bowls are way past "having a moment"—they've become a pillar of our lunches and dinners. Why? It's simple: Everything's better in a bowl! But seriously, the customizable combo of carbs, protein, veggies, and a drizzle of delicious sauce cannot be denied. True to form, this rendition is fully loaded. Buttery, lime-laced jasmine rice is topped with saucy ground pork and tender carrots. It's all drizzled with a delectable chili mayo, then topped with crispy fried onions and fresh cilantro. One bite will have you totally bowled over.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%ounce}, 1¼ cups water, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry all produce. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} with @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%oz} to taste.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground pork{10%oz} and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in @shredded carrots{4%oz}, @sweet soy glaze{4%tbsp}, and @sesame dressing{1.5%oz}. Cook until carrots are softened, pork is cooked through, and sauce has thickened, ~{2-4%minutes} more. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn off heat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest and @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between bowls and top with pork mixture and any remaining sauce from pan. Drizzle with chili mayo. Sprinkle with @crispy fried onions{1} and cilantro. Serve with lime wedges on the side.